<subSubSection id="19D765649927FF9D07B94895AB2F86B5" pageId="38" pageNumber="39" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="517236EF9927FF9D07B94895AB2F86B5" blockId="38.[151,1436,1522,1946]" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">
<emphasis id="63B9EAFD9927FF9D07B94895A9048691" bold="true" box="[199,326,1666,1691]" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">Etymology</emphasis>
. The specific epithet 
<taxonomicName id="96CD4D6C9927FF9D053D4894AAA28691" authority="Latin" authorityName="Latin" box="[579,736,1666,1691]" class="Insecta" family="Empididae" genus="Hemerodromia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="38" pageNumber="39" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="oriens">
<emphasis id="63B9EAFD9927FF9D053D4894AACB8690" box="[579,649,1667,1690]" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">oriens</emphasis>
(Latin)
</taxonomicName>
meaning eastern, reflects the only known occurrence of this species in the east of 
<collectingCountry id="29DA767F9927FF9D06F848B1A9AF86B5" box="[390,493,1702,1727]" name="Thailand" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">Thailand</collectingCountry>
. It is used as a noun in apposition.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="19D765649927FF9D07B948DDACBF8793" pageId="38" pageNumber="39" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="517236EF9927FF9D07B948DDACBF8793" blockId="38.[151,1436,1522,1946]" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">
<emphasis id="63B9EAFD9927FF9D07B948DDA97686E9" bold="true" box="[199,308,1738,1763]" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">Remarks</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName id="96CD4D6C9927FF9D063B48DDAA7D86E8" box="[325,575,1738,1763]" class="Insecta" family="Empididae" genus="Hemerodromia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="38" pageNumber="39" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="oriens" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="63B9EAFD9927FF9D063B48DDAA7D86E8" box="[325,575,1738,1763]" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">Hemerodromia oriens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="788A57869927FF9D053448DDAAE586E9" box="[586,679,1738,1763]" pageId="38" pageNumber="39" rank="species">
<emphasis id="63B9EAFD9927FF9D053448DDAAE586E9" bold="true" box="[586,679,1738,1763]" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
is similar to many other Oriental 
<taxonomicName id="96CD4D6C9927FF9D034348DDACA486E9" box="[1085,1254,1738,1763]" class="Insecta" family="Empididae" genus="Hemerodromia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="38" pageNumber="39" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="63B9EAFD9927FF9D034348DDACA486E9" box="[1085,1254,1738,1763]" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">Hemerodromia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
having a black thorax, pale legs and M 
<number id="E70524C89927FF9D06E248EAA9E38701" box="[412,417,1789,1803]" pageId="38" pageNumber="39" value="1.0">1</number>
+ 
<number id="E70524C89927FF9D06D548EAA9F68701" box="[427,436,1789,1803]" pageId="38" pageNumber="39" value="2.0">2</number>
fork present. The male cercus is narrow in profile but very broad, almost quadrate basally in dorsal view (
<figureCitation id="C9F62A6A9927FF9D063A4902A9D58724" box="[324,407,1813,1838]" captionStart="FIGURES 58 – 59" captionStartId="38.[151,264,1424,1447]" captionTargetBox="[159,1435,675,1397]" captionTargetId="figure@38.[151,1435,666,1403]" captionTargetPageId="38" captionText="FIGURES 58 – 59. Male terminalia of Hemerodromia oriens sp. nov. 58, lateral view of terminalia; 59, dorsal view of cerci. Abbreviations: cer = cerci, epa = epandrium, hyp = hypandrium, ph = phallus." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/289953/files/figure.png" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">
Fig. 
<number id="E70524C89927FF9D06064902A9D58724" box="[376,407,1813,1838]" pageId="38" pageNumber="39" value="58.0">58</number>
</figureCitation>
), quite different from 
<taxonomicName id="96CD4D6C9927FF9D05F04901AC638724" authority="Yang &amp; Yang, 1988" authorityName="Yang &amp; Yang" authorityYear="1988" box="[654,1057,1814,1838]" class="Insecta" family="Empididae" genus="Hemerodromia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="38" pageNumber="39" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="yunnanensis">
<emphasis id="63B9EAFD9927FF9D05F04901AB798727" box="[654,827,1814,1837]" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">H. yunnanensis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="355C4B1E9927FF9D043F4901AC638724" author="Yang" box="[833,1057,1814,1838]" pageId="38" pageNumber="39" refString="Yang, C. &amp; Yang, D. (1988) Six new species of the genus Hemerodromia from China (Diptera: Empididae). Acta Zootaxonomica Sinica, 13, 281 - 286." type="journal article" year="1988">
Yang &amp; Yang, 
<number id="E70524C89927FF9D04984901AC638724" box="[998,1057,1814,1838]" pageId="38" pageNumber="39" value="1988.0">1988</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="96CD4D6C9927FF9D03524901AD2F8724" authority="Yang &amp; Yang, 1986" authorityName="Yang &amp; Yang" authorityYear="1986" box="[1068,1389,1813,1838]" class="Insecta" family="Empididae" genus="Hemerodromia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="38" pageNumber="39" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fusca">
<emphasis id="63B9EAFD9927FF9D03524901ACCB8724" box="[1068,1161,1814,1838]" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">H. fusca</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="355C4B1E9927FF9D03EE4901AD2F8724" author="Yang" box="[1168,1389,1813,1838]" pageId="38" pageNumber="39" refString="Yang, C. &amp; Yang, D. (1986) Fourteen new species of dance flies from Fujian and Guangxi. Wuyi Science Journal, 6, 75 - 88." type="journal article" year="1986">
Yang &amp; Yang, 
<number id="E70524C89927FF9D024B4902AD2F8724" box="[1333,1389,1813,1838]" pageId="38" pageNumber="39" value="1986.0">1986</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="96CD4D6C9927FF9D07E9492DA9358758" box="[151,375,1849,1874]" class="Insecta" family="Empididae" genus="Hemerodromia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="38" pageNumber="39" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="phahompokensis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="63B9EAFD9927FF9D07E9492DA9358758" box="[151,375,1849,1874]" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">H. phahompokensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="63B9EAFD9927FF9D06FE492EA99E8758" bold="true" box="[384,476,1849,1874]" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="788A57869927FF9D06FE492EA99E8758" box="[384,476,1849,1874]" pageId="38" pageNumber="39" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
with which it might otherwise be confused. 
<taxonomicName id="96CD4D6C9927FF9D049B492EAC9C875B" box="[997,1246,1849,1874]" class="Insecta" family="Empididae" genus="Hemerodromia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="38" pageNumber="39" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="oriens" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="63B9EAFD9927FF9D049B492EAC9C875B" box="[997,1246,1849,1874]" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">Hemerodromia oriens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="63B9EAFD9927FF9D0396492EAD068758" bold="true" box="[1256,1348,1849,1874]" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="788A57869927FF9D0396492EAD068758" box="[1256,1348,1849,1874]" pageId="38" pageNumber="39" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
is only known from small shaded streams in lowland deciduous and dry evergreen forests in the eastern province of Mukdahan (
<figureCitation id="C9F62A6A9927FF9D06604996A9308793" box="[286,370,1921,1946]" captionStart="FIGURES 91 – 98" captionStartId="49.[151,264,1887,1910]" captionTargetBox="[281,1307,208,1839]" captionTargetId="figure@49.[264,1331,193,1856]" captionTargetPageId="49" captionText="FIGURES 91 – 98. Distribution of Hemerodromia spp. in Thailand at a resolution of 0.25 ° of latitude and longitude with symbols scaled to 0.5 °. 91, H. ocellata sp. nov.; 92, H. oriens sp. nov.; 93, H. phahompokensis sp. nov.; 94, H. songsee sp. nov.; 95, H. systoechon sp. nov.; 96, H. yunnanensis Yang &amp; Yang; 97, H. zetalutea sp. nov.; 98, Species richness of Hemerodromia spp. in Thailand at a resolution of 1 ° with symbols plotted at same resolution." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/289961/files/figure.png" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">
Fig. 
<number id="E70524C89927FF9D062C4996A9308793" box="[338,370,1921,1945]" pageId="38" pageNumber="39" value="92.0">92</number>
</figureCitation>
). Adults have been captured during November at the start of the cool dry season.
</paragraph>
